ed Kingdom","Morton-on-Swale, Yorkshire, England":"Morton-on-Swale, Yorkshire, England"},"cs":{"1452–11 May 1542":"1452–11. května 1542","1457–1482":"1457–1482","1482–1542":"1482–1542","1482–1548":"1482–1548","1452–1542":"1452–1542","1457":"1457","11 May 1542":"11. května 1542","1542":"1542","11 May 1482":"11. května 1482","1452":"1452","1482":"1482","5 September 1482":"5. září 1482","1548":"1548","Great Bromley, Essex, England":"Great Bromley, Essex, Anglie, United Kingdom","Morton, Derbyshire, England":"Morton, Derbyshire, Anglie, United Kingdom","Morton-on-Swale, Yorkshire, England":"Morton-on-Swale, Yorkshire, Anglie"},"da":{"1452–11 May 1542":"1452–11. maj 1542","1457–1482":"1457–1482","1482–1542":"1482–1542","1482–1548":"1482–1548","1452–1542":"1452–1542","1457":"1457","11 May 1542":"11. maj 1542","1542":"1542","11 May 1482":"11. maj 1482","1452":"1452","1482":"1482","5 September 1482":"5. september 1482","1548":"1548","Great Bromley, Essex, England":"Great Bromley, Essex, England, United Kingdom","Morton, Derbyshire, England":"Morton, Derbyshire, England, United Kingdom","Morton-on-Swale, Yorkshire, England":"Morton-on-Swale, Jórvík, England"},"nl":{"1452–11 May 1542":"1452–11 mei 1542","1457–1482":"1457–1482","1482–1542":"1482–1542","1482–1548":"1482–1548","1452–1542":"1452–1542","1457":"1457","11 May 1542":"11 mei 1542","1542":"1542","11 May 1482":"11 mei 1482","1452":"1452","1482":"1482","5 September 1482":"5 september 1482","1548":"1548","Great Bromley, Essex, England":"Great Bromley, Essex, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Morton, Derbyshire, England":"Morton, Derbyshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Morton-on-Swale, Yorkshire, England":"Morton-on-Swale, Yorkshire, England"},"en":{"1452–11 May 1542":"1452–11 May 1542","1457–1482":"1457–1482","1482–1542":"1482–1542","1482–1548":"1482–1548","1452–1542":"1452–1542","1457":"1457","11 May 1542":"11 May 1542","1542":"1542","11 May 1482":"11 May 1482","1452":"1452","1482":"1482","5 September 1482":"5 September 1482","1548":"1548","Great Bromley, Essex, England":"Great Bromley, Essex, England, United Kingdom","Morton, Derbyshire, England":"Morton, Derbyshire, England, United Kingdom","Morton-on-Swale, Yorkshire, England":"Morton-on-Swale, Yorkshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Clark","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: from Middle English <i>clerk</i>, <i>clark</i> ‘clerk, cleric, writer’ (Old French <i>clerc</i>; see   Clerc  ). The original sense was ‘man in a religious order, cleric, clergyman’. As all writing and secretarial work in medieval Christian Europe was normally done by members of the clergy, the term <i>clerk</i> came to mean ‘scholar, secretary, recorder, or penman’ as well as ‘cleric’. As a surname, it was particularly common for one who had taken only minor holy orders. In medieval Christian Europe, clergy in minor orders were permitted to marry and so found families; thus the surname could become established.","Irish (Westmeath, Mayo): in Ireland the English surname was frequently adopted, partly by translation for <i>Ó Cléirigh</i>; see   Cleary  .","Americanized form of Dutch   De Klerk   or Flemish   De Clerck   or of variants of these names, and possibly also of French   Clerc  . Compare   Clerk   2 and   De Clark  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Clarke","meanings":["English and Irish: variant of   Clark  .","History: This name was brought independently to New England by many bearers from the 17th century onward. Nicholas Clarke was one of the founders of Hartford, CT (coming from Cambridge, MA with Thomas Hooker) in 1635."]},{"name":"Clerk","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Pierre, Jacques.","English: variant of   Clark  .","Americanized form of French   Clerc   and perhaps also of the Dutch and Flemish cognates   De Klerk   and   De Clerck   or of variants of these names. Compare   Clark   3."]},{"name":"Clerkin","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Liam, Brendan, Dympna, Seamus.","Irish (Monaghan): from an Irish pet form of English <i>clerk</i> ‘cleric’ (Irish <i>cléireach</i>), see   Clark  . Alternatively, an Anglicized form of <b>Ó Cléireacháin</b>, ‘descendant of little cleric’, an Irish diminutive of the word. See also   McClurkin  , an Antrim surname from <i>Mac Cléirchín</i> ‘son of little cleric’."]},{"name":"Calarco","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Rocco, Angelo, Carmelo, Fausto, Nunziato, Salvatore.","Italian (southern): probably a nickname derived from Greek <i>kalē archē</i> ‘good beginning’. Compare   Clark   4."]},{"name":"Clerc","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Alain, Odette, Sebastien, Serge.","French: occupational or status name for a member of a minor religious order or for a scholar, Old French <i>clerc</i>, from Late Latin <i>clericus</i>, from Greek <i>klērikos</i>, a derivative of <i>klēros</i> ‘inheritance, legacy’, with reference to the priestly tribe of Levites (see   Levy  ) ‘whose inheritance was the Lord’. In medieval Christian Europe, clergy in minor orders were permitted to marry and so found families; thus the surname could become established. In the Middle Ages it was virtually only members of religious orders who learned to read and write, so that the term <i>clerc</i> later came to denote any literate man, a scholar (hence its modern meaning ‘scribe, secretary’ or ‘clerk’). Compare   Leclerc  ."]},{"name":"Clarkson","meanings":["English (Lancashire and Yorkshire): patronymic from   Clark  ."]}]},{"name":"Morton","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Transferred use of the surname, in origin a local name from any of the numerous places so called from Old English <i>mōrtūn</i> ‘settlement by or on a moor’. It is also widely used as a Jewish name, having been adopted as an approximate English equivalent of   Moses ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Morton Clark was born in 1452, in Morton, Derbyshire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 2 daughters with Joan Jackson. He died on 11 May 1542, in his hometown, at the age of 90."},"et":{"1452–11 May 1542":"1452–11. mai 1542","1457–1482":"1457–1482","1482–1542":"1482–1542","1482–1548":"1482–1548","1452–1542":"1452–1542","1457":"1457","11 May 1542":"11. mai 1542","1542":"1542","11 May 1482":"11. mai 1482","1452":"1452","1482":"1482","5 September 1482":"5. september 1482","1548":"1548","Great Bromley, Essex, England":"Great Bromley, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Morton, Derbyshire, England":"Morton, Derbyshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Morton-on-Swale, Yorkshire, England":"Morton-on-Swale, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"1452–11 May 1542":"1452–11. toukokuuta 1542","1457–1482":"1457–1482","1482–1542":"1482–1542","1482–1548":"1482–1548","1452–1542":"1452–1542","1457":"1457","11 May 1542":"11. toukokuuta 1542","1542":"1542","11 May 1482":"11. toukokuuta 1482","1452":"1452","1482":"1482","5 September 1482":"5. syyskuuta 1482","1548":"1548","Great Bromley, Essex, England":"Great Bromley, Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Morton, Derbyshire, England":"Morton, Derbyshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Morton-on-Swale, Yorkshire, England":"Morton-on-Swale, Yorkshire, England"},"fr":{"1452–11 May 1542":"1452–11 mai 1542","1457–1482":"1457–1482","1482–1542":"1482–1542","1482–1548":"1482–1548","1452–1542":"1452–1542","1457":"1457","11 May 1542":"11 mai 1542","1542":"1542","11 May 1482":"11 mai 1482","1452":"1452","1482":"1482","5 September 1482":"5 septembre 1482","1548":"1548","Great Bromley, Essex, England":"Great Bromley, Essex, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Morton, Derbyshire, England":"Morton, Derbyshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Morton-on-Swale, Yorkshire, England":"Morton-on-Swale, Everwyck, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Morton Clark est né en 1452, à Morton, Derbyshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 2 filles avec Joan Jackson. Il est 